                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Thompson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-06-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>April 12, 1893, the Brazilian minister of foreign affairs agreed with Conger the
                    duty on American flour should cease, and duties previously collected be
                    refunded.</p>
                <p>Levering &amp; Co., of Bio de Janeiro, and others have claims for duties so
                    exacted, and which Brazil has not satisfied.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to call the attention of Brazilian Government, and report upon
                    result.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
